{code}
git status --porcelain --untracked-files=no --ignore-submodules=dirty
{code}

{code}
git log --max-count=200  --branches --tags --remotes --full-history --topo-order --decorate=full --date=iso HEAD --
{code}

Using the command line from within ST using embedded GIT also produces long delay.

Running these using system GIT, or Putty outside of Sourcetree does not produce this issue.

{quote}
When I stage a file for a commit, a loading sphere appears for a second, and the "Push changes immediately to <repo>" checkbox goes white. After that second passes, everything's fine, but if I push the commit button in that one-second period, right after staging, it hangs the program.
{quote}

This affects vertical sidebar for REPOS >> project tab.

Affects repos that have over 100 remote branches.

To reproduce the bug:
1. Pull one of the states of the main branch to local by double clicking on it;
2. Pull another one in the end of the list from another branch;
3. In that moment the list will be cut off and a lot of records in vertical list become unavailable.
